Engaged Sessions, Bot Billing, and Bot Performance

Use engaged sessions to track your bot use against your monthly subscription allowance and measure bot performance.

Einstein Bots uses engaged sessions to differentiate between conversations with and without two-way interaction between your customer and your bot. An engaged session is any bot conversation where your customer sends at least one message or selects at least one menu option or choice other than the End Chat button.

All sessions on third-party channels count as engaged sessions because a bot conversation is always initiated by your customer.

On all channels, a bot-to-bot transfer counts as a single engaged session for the initiating bot. For example, when Bot A transfers the conversation to Bot B, it counts as a single engaged session against Bot A only.

Bot Billing

You receive 25 Einstein Bots conversations per month for each active Digital Engagement user. You can buy a subscription for an additional 100 Einstein Bots conversations per month for use in one org. Conversations must be used within a given calendar month and don't roll over to subsequent calendar months.

For billing purposes, one engaged session equals one bot conversation. Only engaged sessions count against your monthly subscription allowance. A session in which your customer ends the conversation before interacting with the bot isn’t counted as an engaged session and doesn’t count against your allowance.

To track your bot use against your monthly subscription allowance, view your engaged session count in Usage-based Entitlements.

Bot Performance

Dig into how your customers are using your bot with engaged session metric types and reports. We provide several prebuilt standard reports that give you insight into how often customers are engaging with your bot, the average length of time customers spend talking to your bot, and more.
